==English==

===Verb===
to invaginate (third-person singular simple present [[invaginates]], present participle [[invaginating]], simple past [[invaginated]], past participle [[invaginated]]).
#{{medicine}} {{cattag|surgery}} To fold up or enclose into a sheath-like or pouch-like structure, either naturally or as part of a surgical procedure.
#{{medicine}} To turn or fold inwardly.
#{{medicine}} Infolding to create a hollow space where none had existed, as with a [[gastrula]] forming from a [[blastula]].

